e generator. This is yet another improvement to my static websites. Jekyll allows me to maintain my website easily. It’s a great to have feature for developers who want to manage static websites. And, wah lah! Here you go my latest website. Now, it’s time to push even further. Having now mastered the basics of responsive web design, it’s time to add icing on the cake - add animation and other features to my websites. It’s also time to learn WordPress development. WordPress is a good place to start learning dynamic web development. It has been a while since the last time I designed and built a fully functional dynamic web app. It’s time to refresh the skills and learn more about it. This is exactly what I’m going to do next. Following the previous announcements on making web development a lifetime passion and learning to design, construct and publish dynamic websites and web-based applications with WordPress, I must manage my time and resources well so that I have ample time to acquire these fascinating knowledge, tools and skills. To record my progress, I will update you my learning journey in this blog. You will see more about web programming here! "
